lzh_formatted:
  title: 途中卽事
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 一逕靑苔濕馬蹄。蟬聲斷續路高低。窮村婦女猶多思。笑整荊釵照柳溪。
korean:
  title: 도중 즉사
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: |-
    한 줄기 오솔길의 푸른 이끼는 말 발굽에 젖는데
    매미소리는 끊어졌다 이어졌다, 길은 높았다 낮았다
    산골의 색시는 생각이 많아
    웃으며 나무 비녀 바로잡으면서 버들 개울에 비쳐보네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0660&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Impressions on the Road
  author: Kim Geuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A single path, green with moss, grows damp beneath the horse's hooves.
    Cicada songs break and resume as the road rises and falls.
    The village girl, her mind adrift in reverie,
    Smiles as she adjusts her wooden hairpin, gazing at her reflection in the willow creek.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The wooden hairpin (荊釵) traditionally signified a modest maiden, contrasting with the elaborate ornaments of the wealthy
  - key: ''
    value: The willow creek serves as both a literal mirror and a symbol of fleeting beauty and reflection
